news.title: Asian Development Bank approves $190 million loan for Indore Metro rail project
news.para: The Asian Development Bank (ADB) has approved a USD 190 million loan to support the development of the Indore Metro Rail Project, a transformative initiative aimed at enhancing urban mobility, reducing pollution, and promoting inclusive growth in Madhya Pradesh, as per a company press release.

news.title: Australia's home prices rise at fastest clip in a year as rate cuts fuel demand
news.para: Australian home prices surged 0.8% in September, marking the fastest annual pace to a record median value, driven by rate cuts and low listings. Strong buyer demand and a new first home buyer policy are expected to further boost prices through spring, while the rental market also tightens.

news.title: Vacate 16 unsafe buildings in 24 hours: Jaipur civic body to owners
news.para: Jaipur Municipal Corporation Heritage took swift action against unsafe buildings in Walled City, serving notices to 16 owners to vacate within 24 hours. They also demolished parts of two buildings, sealed several others, and ordered repairs for nine, deploying staff for continuous monitoring to prevent rain-related incidents and ensure public safety.

news.title: Sand not cheaper in Rajasthan even two years after new mining leases
news.para: Jaipur residents still face high sand prices despite the state government's two-year-old promise of cheaper supply through new mining blocks. Illegal extraction continues, and even recently issued 100-hectare leases are plagued by irregularities and operational delays, with leaseholders prioritizing transit pass sales over actual sand supply.

news.title: Gurugram civic body razes illegal commercial building
news.para: Gurugram authorities demolished an illegal commercial building on Wednesday. The structure belonged to Congress functionary Rajesh Yadav. The demolition drive turned tense during the action. Yadav confronted the enforcement team. He alleged political motivation behind the move. Officials stated the demolition was lawful. Police escorted Yadav from the site. He later apologized for his actions.

news.title: Delhi: No power, water at Signature View Apartments from October 13
news.para: Civic agencies will discontinue water and electricity to Signature View Apartments on October 13, enforcing a Delhi High Court deadline for residents to vacate by October 12. The MCD declared the complex dangerous last year, a decision upheld by the High Court, allowing DDA to proceed with redevelopment after IIT-Delhi recommended dismantling due to structural flaws.

news.title: Telangana RERA imposes fines on three developers for project delays
news.para: The Telangana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (TGRERA) penalized three developers for failing to deliver projects on time and violating RERA Act provisions. Penalties included significant fines, orders to refund substantial amounts with interest for unstarted projects, and directives to execute sale deeds for delayed possessions, ensuring consumer protection.

news.title: Rajasthan government tells limestone leaseholders to obtain approvals fast
news.para: Rajasthan government has mandated all mineral block leaseholders, particularly cement companies, to expedite necessary clearances for operationalizing auctioned sites. Officials warned against delays and incomplete documentation, emphasizing that bringing these blocks into operation is a top priority. A strict warning was issued to firms extracting minerals without proper approvals.

news.title: India’s first 3D-printed rural home comes up in Roorkee
news.para: India's first 3D concrete-printed rural house, developed under Pradhan Mantri Awaas Yojana–Gramin, was inaugurated at CBRI Roorkee. This prototype offers a fast, affordable, and sustainable housing solution for villages, built in under a week for Rs 1.8 lakh using eco-friendly materials. It marks a significant step towards scalable, environmentally responsible rural housing.

news.title: Citing partial OC from MCD, Delhi RERA brings old project handed over in 2008 under its ambit
news.para: Delhi RERA has directed state-run NBCC to register its 17-year-old Saket Plaza Complex as an 'ongoing project'. This order follows NBCC's failure to execute conveyance deeds and obtain a full completion certificate, despite allottees receiving possession years ago. The authority mandated registration, a valid completion certificate, and allottee association formation within 90 days.

news.title: Navi Mumbai International Airport inauguration on October 8
news.para: Gautam Adani announced the Navi Mumbai International Airport's inauguration on October 8, following its recent aerodrome licence approval. This second Mumbai airport, a joint venture with CIDCO, is being developed in phases to become a major Asian hub, capable of serving 90 million passengers annually upon full completion.

news.title: Delhi government initiates process for circle rate revision, seeks public feedback
news.para: The Delhi government has initiated the revision of circle rates for properties across the city, a decade after the last update in 2014. This move aims to align property valuations with current market conditions and enhance transparency in transactions.

news.title: ED attaches over ₹10-crore assets of Ansal Properties' promoters
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has attached six properties worth Rs 10.55 crore belonging to directors and shareholders of Ansal Properties and Infrastructure Ltd, including Sushil Ansal. This action, under anti-money laundering law, follows alleged violations of environmental protection acts in two Gurugram real estate projects.

news.title: Insolvency professionals, valuers need very effective self-regulating mechanism: Official
news.para: Corporate Affairs Secretary Deepti Gaur Mukerjee emphasized self-regulation for insolvency professionals and valuers. She spoke at the IBBI's ninth annual day event. Mukerjee stated the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code faces high expectations. IBBI Chairperson Ravi Mital reported over one lakh homebuyers received benefits from the Code. He also mentioned 125 amendments to IBBI regulations.

news.title: IKEA buys $213 million Manhattan building for new store in US push
news.para: Ingka Group, the largest global IKEA retailer, acquired a 53,000 square feet Manhattan property in SoHo for $213 million. This purchase is part of its $2.2 billion U.S. expansion, planning a new two-story IKEA store and office rentals. This move continues IKEA's recent strategy of opening stores in major city centers.

news.title: Land Beat app flags 1.5 lakh land parcels under encroachment in Karnataka
news.para: Karnataka's 'Land Beat' app has identified 1.5 lakh parcels, spanning 14.1 lakh acres, as encroached government land. This digital initiative empowers village accountants to geo-fence and verify plots, aiming to reclaim public property. The state has already recovered Rs 5,000 crore worth of land in Bengaluru, with other states now studying Karnataka's model to combat widespread land encroachment effectively.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves policy to double Global Capacity Centres by 2030
news.para: Maharashtra's cabinet approved a new policy to attract investments in Global Capacity Centres (GCCs), aiming to double their number to 800 by 2030. This initiative targets Tier-2 and Tier-3 cities, seeking Rs 50,600 crore investment and creating four lakh new jobs through various incentives. The policy expects to boost diverse sectors.

news.title: Income tax department's lens on property deals worth ₹28,000 crore in Manesar
news.para: An I-T survey found serious documentation lapses at Manesar tehsil, where PAN details were missing from property transaction records worth Rs 28,000 crore over five years. This widespread issue, affecting 93 tehsils due to software glitches, raises concerns about potential large-scale tax evasion and undermines transparency.

news.title: Future-Proof Realty Ep 2: The next chapter in India’s green building story
news.para: India's real estate sector, a significant contributor to global emissions, is rapidly shifting towards sustainability to achieve net-zero by 2070. The green building market is projected to double by 2030, adopting innovative practices like solar power and sustainable materials.
